Selling my rifle.  It's a newer Waffen Werks/DDI AK74 in 5.45x39mm.

Waffen Werks had problems in 2013 but DDI bought them out and rebuilt most of their rifles on in-spec receivers.  They are still honoring past warranties and so far all DDI rebuilds have been pretty top notch. This one was rebuilt by DDI.  It passes the bullet test and seems to be put together very well. This rifle did not perform well with Red Army Standard 69gr 5.45x39mm.  If you read online you can see others are having issues with the same ammo. I would stay away from RAS 69gr.  Performed flawlessly with Wolf 60gr 5.45x39mm.

title: For Sale/Trade:  One of a kind Type-M bullpup
postcontent:
The rifle is a Type-M (NR) (sks that takes AK mags from the factory) I bought a year or two ago for $600, I had a master craftsman build the walnut stock and then coat in ebony and he cut down the rail all for about $300.

Short Video of my brother shooting it: https://www.facebook.com/7.62x39fans or http://www.discountfiling.com/SS/ (One is bound to work)

The muzzle device accepts Chevy oil filters (not saying I would ever do it legal eagles) (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=29-qI9WnQco). Up top is a Primary Arms optic and I just installed a Magpul buttpad which gives a perfect feel.

I cut the barrel down to 16.25" (OA 26.25") with the brake permanently attached to the threaded and crowned barrel. I removed the strap lug and blended that smoothly also.

I finished it in Graphite Black Cerakote. I had it notched it to accept 30 rd mags but found them impossible to change so I have the 4 hard to find tanker mags that do the job, 2 of them have weak springs, they had a few hiccups when they got down to the last rounds and the other two did perfect. (Just found out 20 rd tapcos are available and cheap) The railed gas tube on it to hold the optic was loose but some AR rings made a perfect reliable seal and the factory one comes with it also that does not need the rings. 

The gun is a ton of fun to shoot and the trigger feels good. I tried to include everything I could think of but ask me anything you can think of.
I am a little leery parting with it but have more fun building stuff than anything.

title: For Sale:  CZ P07 Duty
postcontent:
Extended barrel, two-15 rd mags, night sights, pistol lock, no box or case. This has the safety with no decocker so it's single-action only. What you see in the pics is what you'd be buying.

Hard to let go but my interest is shifting slowly but surely to another caliber. Had the gun since March, been nothing but reliable. I won't deceive by saying "low round count" to try squeezing more money out of you. Since March there have been many range sessions where I've put it through it's paces and I have not been disappointed in the least. There was even a two and a half month period where I didn't shoot it; left it in Vegas while I PCS'd here until I went back on leave and got it. The next time I shot the gun it did not miss a beat. I'd estimate 900-1000 rds through it: zero malfunctions! Great pistol...it's a CZ.

I realize money is tight for many people so as usual I'm willing to give a great deal, $375 firm. I'm the original owner, bought it for almost twice what I'm selling it for. My experience, if Glock is supposedly the standard for reliability this CZ has exceeded that (I had a Glock 19 that stove-piped about 7 times in a thousand rounds). My hope is that the next owner is someone in need of a good, reliable self/home defense gun. This is the one for you. 

I haven't even mentioned that this feels GREAT in the hand!

No shipping. If you're in the vicinity of either Pensacola or Fort Walton Beach I can drive to you but will not go any further. No trades. $375 firm. Email or text REDACTED. Thanks for looking.

Edit: Serious inquiries only. Not trying to be mean, just asking you to please do your research before contacting me. Had a gentleman think this was a full size comparable to a Glock 17 but it's actually a compact like the G19. 
I forgot to include them in the pics, will also add a pistol lock and an Uplula speed loader which I bought for $34. Does not alter the selling price, still $375.  Thanks.

title: For Sale:  EAA Tangfoglio Witness P Compact .45
postcontent:
I have a used EAA Tangfoglio Witness P(Polymer) Compact .45 for sale. It's a full framed polymer compact made by Tangfoglio and imported by EAA. It is one of the first polymer framed versions imported(according to the serial number). I would rate the cosmetic condition 7.5/10 and the performance/parts condition 9/10. It shows some age with the bluing fading a little and some scratches/markings on the slide, but functionability is perfect and it shoots where it aims. It has a 3.6" barrel, 8-rd mag, weighs less than 30 oz unloaded, is very concealable, and has a great DA/SA pull despite the low retail price. The SA is better than any gun I've ever shot/owned(in my opinion), and that includes a couple sigs, an hk, and my FNH FNP-40. It is a lot of gun for the price and is able to accept 10-rd mags and 14-rd mags(I haven't personally tried the 14), so can still be a carry .45 with 10 or 14 round magazines. 

I may be interested in trades, but cash talks louder. $400 straight cash price for the gun and 1-8 rd magazine.
